sentences: He started his career in 1974 with a duet song.
Nayyar and Akhlaq Ahmed remained dominant playback singers of the Pakistani film industry in the late 1970s and throughout the 1980s.
He graduated with a BEd degree from the Government Central Training College in 1975.
Nayyar's first appearance on TV was on the show Naye Fankar in 1974 after which he began his playback singing journey.
He was introduced to Lollywood by Riaz Shahid, a noted filmmaker of the time, who was searching for a singing talent for his upcoming venture Bahisht (1974).
